    <div id = "page_Contents">
      <h1>Stack and Heap</h1>
      <div>
          <img src="images/post1cc.jpg" width = 500dp>
      </div>
      <p class = "content_Title">Basic</p>
      <p>
        One way of Computer use memory <br>
        when we run code, <br>
        uninitialized global,static variables are allocated in bss<br>
        initialized global,static variables are allocated in data<br>
        And while we run code, <br>
        computer provide memory stack, heap
      </p>
      <p class = "content_Title">Stack</p>
      <div>
          <img src="images/post2cc.jpg" width = 500dp>
      </div>
      <p>
        In code when functions runnig <br>
        Functions take stack memory in order <br>
        Autometicaly,when functions end, where they take, is emtpy<br>
      </p>
      <p class = "content_Title">Heap</p>
      <div>
          <img src="images/post3cc.jpg" width = 500dp>
      </div>
      <p>
        Stack is smaller than heap<br>
        Functions in stack, need more memory like array <br>
        Os assign prefer memory in Heap and tell the 'address' to pointer Valiable in stack<br>
        this way is occured when we use 'new' in code<br>
        But, heap isn't empty Autometicaly, doesn't like stack's way<br>
        In c++ ,you must use 'delete' to empty memory<br>
      </p>
      <p class = "content_Title">Memory leak</p>
      <div>
          <img src="images/post4cc.jpg" width = 500dp>
      </div>
      <p>
        When Function is over in stack, the Poiter variables has heap memory address also gone<br>
        How we can access heap memory? we doesn't have address <br>
        This is memory leak, memory in heap exist, but code can't access<br>
        Nowadays, many languages use Garbage Colloection because that reason <br>
      </p>

